Package: libff1
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Embeddable Forth interpreter (runtime library)
 ff is a compact, embeddable Forth interpreter written in ISO C17.
 It is delivered as a library that routes I/O through caller-supplied
 callbacks and drives the interpreter via ff_eval().
 .
 This package contains the shared library used at runtime by
 applications linked against ff.

Package: libff-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends:
    libff1 (= ${binary:Version}),
    ${misc:Depends}
Description: Embeddable Forth interpreter (development files)
 ff is a compact, embeddable Forth interpreter written in ISO C17.
 .
 This package contains the static library, the public and internal
 (_p.h) headers needed to embed the engine or define new native words,
 and the CMake package config so downstream projects can pick the
 library up via find_package(ff).

Package: libff-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Embeddable Forth interpreter (documentation)
 ff is a compact, embeddable Forth interpreter written in ISO C17.
 .
 This package contains the HTML reference manual generated by Doxygen
 and the typeset PDF reference (ff-reference.pdf).
